  <title>Clutter.TextBuffer::deleted-text</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
def callback(text_buffer, position, n_chars, user_param1, ...)
</code></synopsis>
<p>This signal is emitted after text is deleted from the buffer.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>text_buffer :</p></td>
<td><p>instance of Clutter.TextBuffer that is emitting the signal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>position :</p></td>
<td><p>the position the text was deleted at.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>n_chars :</p></td>
<td><p>The number of characters that were deleted.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>user_param1 :</p></td>
<td><p>first user parameter (if any) specified with the connect() method</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>... :</p></td>
<td><p>additional user parameters (if any)</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.10</p>
</page>
